        <abstract>
            <p>Thanks for her letter of March, which gave him his first explanation of the interest in the [Megatherium] head he had sent.</p>
            <p>Wants E. A. Darwin to tell William Clift not to remove numbers or markers on any specimens. The British Museum has first claim on any of his specimens; CD cannot at present say where any should go.</p>
        </abstract>
